        <p class="text-text-light leading-relaxed"><strong>Summary:</strong> Product loss during discharge is inherent to the self-cleaning disc centrifuge design — it cannot be eliminated entirely, but it can be controlled. In a well-optimized system, discharge loss is kept below 0.1–0.5% of total throughput. Poorly optimized systems can lose 2–5% or more, making product loss a significant operating cost in high-value applications such as clarified oil, yeast, or biological broths.</p>
